BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NmQHRoiPuLFQzP2dl2yXk
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260320T020830Z
DTSTART:20260328T070000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-28T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-28T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wSShhJT6_2yRhmEigURPX
SUMMARY:BiggerPockets Value-Add Conference
DTSTAMP:20260320T020830Z
DTSTART:20260328T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:Real estate investors looking to sharpen their execution and sc
	ale for smarter deals will not want to miss the **first-ever BiggerPockets
	 Value-Add Conference** in Seattle on March 28\, 2026. This one-day\, tigh
	t-knit event has only 120 seats available and is designed specifically for
	 experienced investors actively executing deals.\n\nLed by seasoned local 
	investor and Million Dollar Zombie Flips host James Dainard\, alongside Bi
	ggerPockets experts Dave Meyer and Henry Washington\, the conference offer
	s a rare opportunity to learn how top investors scale deals in today’s com
	petitive real estate market through stronger underwriting\, strategic reno
	vations\, optimized financing\, and disciplined execution systems.\n\nInve
	stment to attend the one-day conference starts at $500\, with a limited nu
	mber of spots available HERE. \n\nThe in-person event features powerful sp
	eakers\, delivering  practical\, action-based strategies investors can imp
	lement immediately\, including:\n\nTeam building and legal structure for s
	ustainable growth\n\nUnderwriting and deal structuring across asset types\
	n\nCapital stack and financing strategies (hard money\, DSCR\, BRRRR)\n\nC
	onstruction and project management systems that protect margins\n\nRenovat
	ions and design decisions that directly impact ROI\n\nScaling operations w
	ith stronger vendor management and streamlined processes\n\nThis experienc
	e is designed for investors with three or more completed deals who are act
	ively executing BRRRRs\, flips\, or small-scale development projects and l
	ooking to build repeatable\, scalable systems. With Seattle’s competitive 
	housing market and continued investor activity\, the conference offers tim
	ely insight into how local operators are navigating tighter margins\, risi
	ng costs\, and evolving financing strategies.\n\nIn addition to the confer
	ence\, on March 29\, a limited Premium Property Tour will take attendees i
	nside active Seattle investment properties\, where James and the speakers 
	will walk through real deals and answer questions in small groups.\n\nhttp
	s://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/biggerpockets-value-add-conferen
	ce/18297942/2026-03-28T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/biggerpockets-value-add-c
	onference/18297942/2026-03-28T00
LOCATION:Seattle\, Wa\, 98121\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT9H
END:VEVENT
